cs.CV, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.NE, cs.MM 

The paper deals with the problem of learning visual similarities in an unsupervised manner, which is a core problem in computer vision. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition). The paper also proposes a single optimization problem to extract batches of samples with mutually consistent relations, which involves training a Convolutional Neural Network (CNN). This suggests that the paper could also belong to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the recent breakthrough in deep learning, which indicates that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper evaluates the proposed approach on posture analysis and object classification, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.MM (Multimedia).
